[{"id":"VH991466","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">When computing a confidence interval for the slope of a regression line, a plot of the residuals versus the fitted values can be used to check which of the following conditions?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH991466_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The variables <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"y\"><math alttext=\"y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>y</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> are inversely related.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The standard deviation of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"y\"><math alttext=\"y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>y</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> does not vary as <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mstyle><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow></mstyle></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> varies.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The correlation is not equal to zero.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The observations are independent.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The confidence interval contains zero.</p>"],"answer":1}]